## README

This folder contains code to replicate Figure 4 and Figure S7.

### Content

Main scripts
- `run_Chloris.R`: the main R script to run Chloris model on melanoma data 
- `plot_Melanoma_genes.R`: R script to summarise consistency with melanoma genes in existing literature. 
- `get_sbatch.R`: an R script to configure and generate `run_sims.sh`

Datasets
- `M71.Rdata`: RDR and BAF 
- `Melanoma_genes.xlsx`: Record of reported melanoma-related genes and supporting literature.

### Workflow

1. In R, source `run_Chloris.R` to get `Chloris_fullmode.rds` and `Chloris_fullmode.png` (Figure 4, left panel)
   
2. In R, source `plot_Melanoma_genes.R` to get `Melanoma_gene_count.pdf` (Figure 4, right panel)

3. In R, source `DE.R`, then source `plot_DE.R` to get `Hallmark_toclone1.png` (Figure S7)

